<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.512/44.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s telegram April 22. I consider that the temporary withholding
                            of consent to stamp tax would still be useful as a means of securing
                            complete observance by China of our treaty rights in respect to inland
                            taxation. See my despatch No. 588.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>